'''Thengling''' is a name used in the [[Song of the Mounds of Mundburg]] poems, used in reference to [[Théoden]]'s death at the [[Battle of the Pelennor Fields]]. It identifies Théoden by his father [[Thengel]]'s name with the diminuative ending 'ling' to denote him being Thengel's child.<ref>{{RK|V6}}, p. 849</ref>
